Best Practices for Clustering
Choose High-Cardinality Columns: Columns with many distinct values (e.g., customer_id) are good candidates for clustering.
      2. Combine with Partitioning
       3.Limit Clustering Columns: Use up to 4 columns for clustering to avoid diminishing returns.
4.Avoid Frequent Updates: Clustering works best for tables with infrequent updates, as BigQuery needs to reorganize data when changes occur.

